\begin_layout Section
Conclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper presents a comparison of correlation based connectivity measures
 and addresses the question what connectivity measure should be used for
 fMRI based connectivity analysis.
 It is also pointed out in this paper that the popularly used spatial connectivi
ty based similarity measure does not provide good performance and is also
 computationally more expensive.
 The spatial connectivity map used in that method as a feature in fact does
 not contain any additional information than the original time series, despite
 being a very high dimensional feature compared to the original time series.
 A new measure of connectivity is suggested and evaluated in this paper
 based on geodesic distance.
 A quantitative performance provides evidence that the proposed geodesic
 distance measure performs best for connectivity studies.
 
\end_layout

